						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone built into the wall of Kalamēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1248.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1171, Kīlaka, Chaitra, ba. 3, Sunday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1248, March 14.</hi> The weekday, however, was Saturday Śaka year being current.</p>						

						<p>The inscription seems to record the death of a person (name lost) during a fight (cattle raid) against Jōyidēva of <hi rend="bold">Gutoḷa</hi> at the instance of Chaṭṭayadēva. It refers to <hi rend="italic">anādi-agrahāra</hi> Kundugoḷa. Other details are lost. Cf. No. 329 below.</p>						

						</summary>
